## 7. Progress Tracking Convention

### In `roadmap.md`
- Phase heading: `### Phase Xa: Name (Weeks N-M) [DONE]`
- Component row: append ` [DONE]` to deliverable cell

### In `specs/phases/phase-{nn}-{id}.md` (phase spec)
- Task = row in Component table (`[x]` or `[ ]`)
- Phase-level overview only — no Step details here

### In `specs/phases/phase-{nn}-{id}/T{id}.X.Y.md` (task file)
- Step = checkbox (`- [x]` completed, `- [ ]` pending)
- Steps ARE the acceptance criteria
- Each Task file is self-contained: deps, files, steps, tests, notes

### In `specs/phases/api-surface-index.md` (hub) + `api-surface-L{NN}.md` (per-layer)
- Hub file: Phase→Layer mapping + dependency table (~90 lines, always loaded)
- Layer files: locked APIs grouped by architecture layer (L01–L11)
- Append-only: phase completion appends to the appropriate layer file
- Layer-based loading keeps token cost O(dependent layers) not O(total phases)

### In `todo_list` tool
- Always reflects current session's active Task
- Each todo item = one Step from the current Task
- ID format: `T{phase_id}.{component}.{task}.{step}` for Step-level

