## 8. Phase Sequence Reference

### Phase ID → Filename Mapping Rules

> **Iron rule**: every Phase has exactly one `{nn}` (2-digit sequence) and one `{id}` (slug).
> File paths use `phase-{nn}-{id}` everywhere. No ambiguity.

| Rule | Example | Result |
|---|---|-----|
| Base phase | Phase 2 | `phase-03-2` (nn=03, id=2) |
| Sub-phase (letter) | Phase 1a | `phase-01-1a` (nn=01, id=1a) |
| Sub-phase (letter+number) | Phase 7a-1 | `phase-11-7a1` (nn=11, id=7a1) |
| Sub-phase (letter suffix) | Phase 11b | `phase-18-11b` (nn=18, id=11b) |
| Cooldown | Cooldown #1 | `phase-cd1-cooldown1` (nn=cd1, id=cooldown1) |
| Tech Spike | GPU Trim Spike | `phase-08-spike` (nn=08, id=spike) |

**Slug rules**: lowercase, no hyphens inside `{id}` (use concatenation: `7a-1` → `7a1`).
Task IDs follow the `{id}`: `T7a1.3.2`, `T11b.1.1`, `Tspike.1.1`, `Tcd1.1.1`.

